               <p>1894. <persName id="def1-1894-18420613" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1894-18420613" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1894-18420613" type="surname" value="WEST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1894-18420613" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES WEST</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted for<rs id="t18420613-1894-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18420613-1894-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420613-1894-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18420613-cd-158" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420613-1894-offence-1 t18420613-cd-158"></join>24th of May</rs> 3 trusses of hay, value 6<hi rend="italic">s;.</hi> the goods of <persName id="t18420613-name-934" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-934" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-934" type="surname" value="HARGOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-934" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-934" type="occupation" value="tailor"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420613-1894-offence-1 t18420613-name-934"></join>John Hargood</persName>, his master; and </rs>
                  <persName id="def2-1894-18420613" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1894-18420613" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1894-18420613" type="surname" value="ALLEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1894-18420613" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM ALLEN</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18420613-1894-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18420613-1894-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420613-1894-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>, for receiving the same, well knowing it to have been stolen, against the Statute, &amp;c.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-936" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-936" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-936" type="surname" value="HARGOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-936" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HARGOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a tailor, and live at Stanmore. On the 24th of May I directed West to bind three quarters of a load of hay—two cuts of it were to go to a customer, and the rest <hi rend="italic">to go to</hi> my lawn—it was a little field of three acres, which I buy the crop of—he bound three quarters and three trusses—he accounted for three quarters only—the three trusses were con<lb></lb>cealed in a loft just by—Allen lodged in Mr. Dorey's loft—I had not sold any hay to Dorey—West only charged for binding the three quarters, not for the three trusses.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-937" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-937" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-937" type="surname" value="SHORT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-937" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE SHORT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in Mr. Hargood's service. On the 24th of May I was sent to a Rick belonging to him, to take half a load down to Mr. Law ford—West sent me with three trusses to Mr. Dorey's, <hi rend="italic">to</hi> the shed, and he told me to tell Allen to take them in, and put them into the loft—I was not aware that it was wrong at that time—I saw Allen put one into the loft, and when I went back again the other two were gone—I took half a load to Mrs. Law ford, six trusses of hay to my master's stable, and three trusses of straw—my master gave West 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for binding the hay—West put the hay on my back to take to the shed—he said he should send a truss or two to Mr. Dorey's; he should like to make a good half-day's work; he did not want to go on the common again.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">West. Q.</hi> What did you tell me when you first came <hi rend="italic">to me</hi> with the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184206130167"></xptr>
               <p>pot <hi rend="italic">of</hi> beer? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I told you my master said I mast carry tome hay to the shed if it rained, but it did not rain.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you carry it in consequence of your master saying it was to go there if it rained, or of West sending it to Dorey's on your back? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> His putting it on my back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-938" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-938" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-938" type="surname" value="DOREY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-938" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DOREY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a coachman, living at Great Stan more—I oc<lb></lb>cupy a stable and shed there—Allen was my stable-man. On the 24th of May I got information that there were some trusses of hay in my loft—I had not ordered it—I asked Allen next morning where he got the three trasses of hay he had in the loft—he said he put them from the shed into the loft—I said it was my belief it was Mr. Hargood's, as I understood he had some bound the previous day, and I had sent for him—I ordered Allen to take it back to Mr. Hargood's rick—I had not bought any of Mr. Hargood, or desired Allen to purchase any for me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you understand from Mrs. Dorey that the hay was there? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did—it was before any inquiry was</p>
               <p>made.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-939" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-939" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-939" type="surname" value="HARWOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-939" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HARWOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. On Wednesday, the 25th of May, I went to my father's rick-yard, and found three trusses lying there—from the quality of the hay I believe it to be my father's—I was sent for by Mr. Dorey.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-940" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-940" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-940" type="surname" value="SHORT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-940" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE SHORT</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> He gave me the order to take it to Dorey's almost before he began to cut any.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">West.</hi> I did up three quarters and three trusses of straw; I asked Short if he had carried it all right, and he said "Yes;" I said, "Go and</p>
               <p>ask for the money," and he went and brought me 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
